    "faqs": [
      {
        "question": "Is the test painful?",
        "answer": "No. You only hear soft knocking sounds; earplugs are provided.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "How long before I get results?",
        "answer": "Scans are read the same day; digital reports emailed in 1–3 hours.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I drive home after the scan?",
        "answer": "Yes, unless you take oral sedation (rare for this test).\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Is contrast dye always needed?",
        "answer": "Rarely. Most CSF flow studies are done without gadolinium.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "What if my child needs sedation?",
        "answer": "Pediatric anesthetists at Cadabams Diagnostics provide safe, mild sedation for children under 5.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "What happens if an abnormality is found on my study?",
        "answer": "  If your **MRI Brain CSF Flow Study** reveals any abnormalities, your referring doctor will discuss these findings with you in detail. They will explain the nature of the abnormality, what it means in the context of your symptoms and overall health, and recommend next steps. This could involve further tests, referrals, or treatment plans. The goal is to use the findings to guide your care appropriately."
      }
    ],
